  RFC5130 [label="RFC5130
A Policy Control Mechanism in IS-IS
Using Administrative Tags
2008", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document describes an extension to the IS-IS protocol to add operational capabilities that allow for ease of management and control over IP prefix distribution within an IS-IS domain.  This document enhances the IS-IS protocol by extending the information that an Intermediate System (IS) router can place in Link State Protocol (LSP) Data Units for policy use.  This extension will provide operators with a mechanism to control IP prefix distribution throughout multi-level IS-IS domains. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"]; 

